---
import star from "../images/faq/icon-star.svg";
import plus from "../images/faq/icon-plus.svg";
import minus from "../images/faq/icon-minus.svg";
import bg from "../images/faq/bg-desktop.svg"
---

<style>
  :root {
    --white: hsl(0, 0%, 100%);
    --light-pink: hsl(275, 100%, 97%);
    --grayish-purple: hsl(292, 16%, 49%);
  }

  * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    font-family: "Work Sans", sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  body {
    background-color: var(--light-pink);
    margin: auto;
    font-size: 16px;

    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .faq_span {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-right: 1rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .container {
    width: 700px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .accordion {
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .acc__item:not(:last-child) {
    border-bottom: solid 2px hsl(275, 100%, 97%);
  }

  .acc__label,
  .acc__input,
  .acc__content {
    padding: 10px;
  }

  .acc__input {
    display: none;
  }

  .acc__label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-weight: 700;
    cursor: pointer;
    position: relative;
  }

  .acc__label:hover {
    color: purple;
  }

  .acc__label > span {
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }


  .acc__content {
    color: var(--grayish-purple);
    line-height: 1.6;
    display: none;
  }

  .acc__input:checked ~ .acc__content {
    display: block;
  }

  .acc__item {
    padding: 5px;
  }

  .acc__minus {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Show minus icon when checkbox is checked */
  .acc__input:checked + .acc__label .acc__minus {
    display: inline-block;
  }

  /* Hide plus icon when checkbox is checked */
  .acc__input:checked + .acc__label .acc__plus {
    display: none;
  }

  .bg_img {
    width: 100%;
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    z-index: -1;
  }

  a {
    align-self: flex-start;
    left: 3rem;
    top: 3rem;
    position: absolute;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 100%);
  }

  a:link {
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 100%);
  }

  svg {
    line-height: 1;
    height: 1em;
    width: 1em;
  }
</style>

<head>
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Work+Sans:ital,wght@0,400;1,400;0,600;1,600;0,700;1,700&display=swap"
    type="text/css"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>
<a href="/">
  <svg
    width="24"
    height="24"
    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
    fill="none"
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
  >
    <path
      fill-rule="evenodd"
      clip-rule="evenodd"
      d="M6 22.8787C4.34315 22.8787 3 21.5355 3 19.8787V9.87866C3 9.84477 3.00169 9.81126 3.00498 9.77823H3C3 9.20227 3.2288 8.64989 3.63607 8.24262L9.87868 2.00002C11.0502 0.828445 12.9497 0.828445 14.1213 2.00002L20.3639 8.24264C20.7712 8.6499 21 9.20227 21 9.77823H20.995C20.9983 9.81126 21 9.84477 21 9.87866V19.8787C21 21.5355 19.6569 22.8787 18 22.8787H6ZM12.7071 3.41423L19 9.70713V19.8787C19 20.4309 18.5523 20.8787 18 20.8787H15V15.8787C15 14.2218 13.6569 12.8787 12 12.8787C10.3431 12.8787 9 14.2218 9 15.8787V20.8787H6C5.44772 20.8787 5 20.4309 5 19.8787V9.7072L11.2929 3.41423C11.6834 3.02371 12.3166 3.02371 12.7071 3.41423Z"
      fill="currentColor"></path>
  </svg>
  Home
</a>
<main>
    <img src={bg.src} alt="bg" class="bg_img">
  <div class="container">
    <h1><span class="faq_span"><img src={star.src} alt="Star" /></span>FAQs</h1>
    <div class="accordion">
      <div class="acc__item">
        <input type="checkbox" id="sec1" class="acc__input" />
        <label for="sec1" class="acc__label">
          <p>What is Frontend Mentor, and how will it help me?</p>
          <div class="acc__img">
            <img src={plus.src} alt="plus" class="acc__plus" />
            <img src={minus.src} alt="minus" class="acc__minus" />
          </div>
          
        </label>
        <div class="acc__content">
          <p>
            Frontend Mentor offers realistic coding challenges to help
            developers improve their frontend coding skills with projects in
            HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It's suitable for all levels and ideal
            for portfolio building.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="acc__item">
        <input type="checkbox" id="sec2" class="acc__input" />
        <label for="sec2" class="acc__label">
          Is Frontend Mentor free?
          <div class="acc__img">
            <img src={plus.src} alt="plus" class="acc__plus" />
            <img src={minus.src} alt="minus" class="acc__minus" />
          </div>
        </label>
        <div class="acc__content">
          <p>
            Yes, Frontend Mentor offers both free and premium coding challenges,
            with the free option providing access to a range of projects
            suitable for all skill levels.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="acc__item">
        <input type="checkbox" id="sec3" class="acc__input" />
        <label for="sec3" class="acc__label">
          Can I use Frontend Mentor projects in my portfolio?
          <div class="acc__img">
            <img src={plus.src} alt="plus" class="acc__plus" />
            <img src={minus.src} alt="minus" class="acc__minus" />
          </div>
        </label>
        <div class="acc__content">
          <p>
            Yes, you can use projects completed on Frontend Mentor in your
            portfolio. It's an excellent way to showcase your skills to
            potential employers!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="acc__item">
        <input type="checkbox" id="sec4" class="acc__input" />
        <label for="sec4" class="acc__label">
          How can I get help if I'm stuck on a challenge?
          <div class="acc__img">
            <img src={plus.src} alt="plus" class="acc__plus" />
            <img src={minus.src} alt="minus" class="acc__minus" />
          </div>
        </label>
        <div class="acc__content">
          <p>
            The best place to get help is inside Frontend Mentor's Discord
            community. There's a help channel where you can ask questions and
            seek support from other community members.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
